# 4. WEEKEND GARAGE

An's Father: Here's your Café au lait. Enjoy.
Kohane: Th-Thank you very much.
An: Hm? Where's your apron, Dad? Are you going somewhere?
An's Father: I just got a call that those good coffee beans are in stock. I'll be back in time to open the bar. Keep an eye on things until then, will you?
An: Roger that. We've only got the one customer right now, so take your time.
Kohane: (N-Now it's just the two of us...)
An: Hmm? You're not nervous, are you?
Kohane: Huh? Oh... S-Sorry!
An: Hahaha. Relax, there's no reason to be so uptight. Judging from your uniform, I take it you go to Miyamasuzaka. We're probably about the same age, too.
Kohane: The same age? I-I'm a freshman.
An: I knew it! I'm a 1st year student at Kamiyama High School.
Kohane: You're a 1st year student too? I was sure you were older than me...
An: Hahaha! My name's An Shiraishi. Nice to meet you.
Kohane: Oh, I'm Kohane Azusawa! I-It's nice to meet you, um...Miss Shiraishi.
An: Call me An. We're the same age, after all. You know, I'm really glad you came back, Kohane.
An: This place really doesn't get many female customers. It's mostly guys who look up to my dad.
Kohane: That was your dad who just left, right? I understand he's the owner and a pretty famous musician...
An: That's right! You know your stuff!
Kohane: Oh, I just looked it up online. It said he used to be active in the music scene here on Vivid Street.
An: Yeah, he was for a long time, but he retired about two years ago and opened this place, so a lot of his old friends and fans come by.
Kohane: Is that who those people were that you were singing with before?
An: Yep. They're musicians who are big fans of my dad. They ask me to sing with them at events all the time.
Kohane: Events? Do you sing at a lot of events, then?
An: Yep, sure do. There are a lot of clubs around here, so it's pretty easy to find gigs.
Kohane: That explains why you seem so used to it. You looked so cool when I saw you last time.
An: Last time? Oh, you mean when you stopped by before?
Kohane: Yeah. Y-You were so good! Actually, I-I was hoping to hear you again...
An: Oh, so that's why you came back.
An: In that case, how about I sing a song?!
Kohane: Huh?
An: Oh, it's just me this time, so it won't be quite the same as the mic relay, but here goes.
Kohane: What?! Wh-What should I do? M-My body's not ready...
An: ♪——!
Kohane: !!
Kohane: (This really is completely different than the video. My heart is racing again!)
An: ♪!!!
Kohane: She's so cool!
An: Phew! What did you—hm?
Kohane: You...were so cool! Thank you, An!
Kohane: Especially the part where you were freestyling! The part that goes...
Kohane: ——♪ Then there was that other part where you were like ～～♪
An: !!
Kohane: And the way you ended it...
An: Hey, Kohane. Can you sing?
Kohane: What?
An: Why don't you try singing real quick? Like you did just now. It sounds like you've got the lyrics memorized, too. Here's the mic!
Kohane: W-Wait! I-I can't sing in such a public place!
An: Please?! I really want to hear you sing! Don't worry, I'm sure you'll be great, Kohane!
Kohane: I-If it's just a little, then all right... But...promise you won't laugh, all right?
An: No problem!
Kohane: ——♪
An: !!
An: (I knew it!)
Kohane: ——♪ ——♪
An: (Her rhythm's a little off, and she's not quite singing from the heart, but...)
An: (Her voice! It's gentle, but it also carries in just the right way! But that's not the only thing!)
An: (It just makes me want to sing with her!)
An: ♪ ——! ——! ——!!
Kohane: ——♪ ——♪
Kohane: Huff... Huff... That...felt great!
An: I found you! I've finally found you!
An: Kohane, let's team up!
An: Let's sweep the world off its feet with our performances!
Kohane: Whaaat?!
